description: Augusta Webster thought she was an ordinary girl living an ordinary life in an ordinary town. But that was before the Snabbit-half-snake/half-rabbit-arrived to turn Augusta's world upside down and reveal that she's anything but ordinary.
name: HC

description: The adaptations based on the hit ABC show Castle continue as Derrick Storm's gruesome discovery draws him into an international spectacle! Who is the Fear? What does he want with Derrick? And why is Derrick's father next on his hit list? As the international situation in New York continues to degrade, Derrick reaches out to the one person who may be able to help him: his former handler, Clara Strike. But even if she responds, will she be with him or against him? As the city of Moscow teeters on the verge of a meltdown, Derrick faces the Fear in final battle. Can he prevent World War III - and finally avenge his mother? Don't miss the espionage thriller that has comic-book and Castle fans raving! Collecting CASTLE: A CALM BEFORE STORM #1-5.
name: HC

description: Superman! Superboy! Supergirl! Krypto the Superdog! The entire Superman family is reimagined here in this energetic all-ages graphic novel. Don't miss the heroes of Metropolis fighting such foes as Bizarro, Metallo, Lex Luthor and more in these tales from issues #1-6 of the all-ages series!
name: Volume 1

description: American Reconstruction begins! Can the shattered nation recover after the dramatic events of 'United We Stand'? President Cap takes charge, Thor makes a momentous decision, the Iron Patriot attacks, and Black Widow becomes director of S.H.I.E.L.D.! But as the country slowly rebuilds, President Cap faces a painful reality as he learns who's behind the latest wave of attacks! What is the secret of Scorpio? How will Captain America juggle his duties as president and handle the ever-deadlier Hydra insurgency? And most important, who are the West Coast Ultimates? A new wave of super heroes debuts, but they're directly opposed to President Cap. Can the Ultimates stop this powerful threat? And can the fragile America survive a super-powered battle royale? Collecting ULTIMATE COMICS ULTIMATES #18.1 & #19-24.
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Ultimate Comics Ultimates by Sam Humphries

description: It's a story that will rock the Ultimate Universe's family tree forever as Jimmy Hudson's quest to discover the answers about his past begins! What mission was Wolverine on that led to Jimmy's birth? What is the deadly secret of Project Mother Vine, and why was Wolverine so desperate to shut it down? And as Jimmy hunts ghosts from his past, the ghosts begin hunting him when a mysterious woman with a connection to Logan resurfaces and Jimmy finds himself caught in a brutal life-and-death battle he can't hope to win -against the brother he never knew he had! Jimmy's loyalties are put to the test as a new villain is born. What is the secret Wolverine never shared with his son? Learn the truth here! Collecting ULTIMATE COMICS WOLVERINE #1-4.
name: TPB

description: In Madripoor, Wolverine runs afoul of drug lords peddling a new and lethal substance: What is Thunderbolt, and how does it make its users unstoppable? Then, a Yukon vacation turns deadly when Wolverine encounters the mythical Hunter in Darkness! And when Lady Deathstrike attacks, Wolverine and his old Alpha Flight buddy Puck fall through a time vortex and wind up in 1937 - where they must team up with Ernest Hemingway to fight the Spanish Civil War! Ask not for whom the bell tolls - it tolls for Logan! Lethal Larry Hama's epic Wolverine run begins here, stylishly illustrated by Marc Silvestri (CyberForce, UNCANNY X-MEN)! Plus: In two classic bonus stories, Wolverine battles Apocalypse in the Savage Land and struggles with his own inner demons when he meets the Neuri! Collecting WOLVERINE (1988) #31-37, WOLVERINE: THE JUNGLE ADVENTURE and WOLVERINE: BLOODLUST.
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Wolverine by Larry Hama and Marc Silvestri

description:
Everything SubCulture in one book! Join Jason, Arthur, Noel and the entire Kingdom Comix crew as they live - and enjoy - the geek life in this funny and poignant look at fanboy (and fangirl) culture. This 336-page tome collects the critically-acclaimed four-issue mini-series plus all 501 webcomics published between 2008 and 2012. Also includes dozens of strips from guest artists, pinups, and behind-the-scenes features. Available in Softcover and limited signed & numbered Hardcover editions.

Note: The digital edition (6/26/2013) for this collection was released a week before the print edition (7/3/2013).
name: TPB/HC

description: The Pygmies Strike Back, Part 3 of 5. Oogas group is lost in the Desert! Running out of food and water is bad enough, but will it drive them over the edge of sanity? Kliks group, however, appears to have been saved by their mysterious last-page-arrival from last issue. But nothings that easy in the Pocket God world, right? You can bet there are more troubles and hard times to come for both groups. But at least Kliks group finds out just a bit more about how the Pocket God world works. Now what do they DO with that knowledge? And you KNOW how we love a big last-page-reveal, so dont peek ahead this time! Its a doozy! The Pocket God Comic App is updated frequently with all kinds of FREE extras such as The Pygmy Peril newsletter (which includes free Little Green Men comic short stories), and an EXCLUSIVE re-mastered version of the first Pocket God animated short! And dont forget that PYGMY PERIL #29 is available right NOW! And if you have already downloaded the App itself, then every issue of PYGMY PERIL is absolutely FREE! This issue of the Peril is packed to the gills with the usual whacked-out Fan-Art, freaked-out Fan-Mail, and also the Dangerous Dialog contest! And of course it closes out with those minuscule minions of madness, the LITTLE GREEN MEN!
name: The Pygmies Strike Back Part 3 (of 5)

James Douglas is a high school senior with little to show for his 17 years and no clear future ahead. He finds the only way change will happen is if he makes it happen. But what do James' bizarre, recurring dreams portend?

Collects strips from April 15, 2009 to July 24, 2009.

The Utopian's identity has been uncovered by nosy reporter Michelle Matterson, and Principal Praglin's search for the cloaked crusader is full-on. What's James Douglas to do?

Collects strips from August 5, 2009 to October 9, 2009.

Following the Utopian's very public fight with Nate Aguila, James Douglas is missing! And Michelle Matterson's looking for him. Where is James? Not even he knows, as he endures a life-altering experience that will leave both you and him with more questions than answers.

Collects strips from October 21, 2009 to January 27, 2010.

James Douglas is back from his mysterious disappearance. But more than just his appearance has changed! Strange things are brewing, not the least of which are a new series of disturbing dreams plaguing James' sleep. Everything comes to a head in this final issue!

Collects strips from February 3, 2010 to October 13, 2010.

A group of college kids on a desert-baked road trip take a Native American drug that unlocks their deepest fears. Now, if a teenager and his grandfather from the local reservation can't find them in time, they're going to have to face their own personal terrors, or be consumed by them! The Trip is an Indian drug fueled ride into horror!
name: GN

description: In 1979, Marvel UK launched the weekly Hulk Comic, which featured new stories starring the green goliath produced by up-and-coming British talent including Dave Gibbons (Watchmen), David Lloyd (V for Vendetta), Steve Dillon (Preacher, Wolverine: Origins), John Bolton (Classic X-Men) and Paul Neary (The Ultimates)! Bolstered by the popularity of the live-action TV show, the Hulk was a hot property on both shores, spawning years of UK-created comic and text stories! Now, for the first time in decades, Marvel UKs vaults are opened and these classic tales, most never before seen on US shores, are collected into one massive volume! Collecting Smash! #38; material from Marvel Storybook Annual 1968; material from Hulk Comic #1-6, #9-20 and #26-28; Incredible Hulk Annual: Authorised Edition 1980; Hulk Annual 1981-1985; and The Super Heroes Annual 1991, written by Steve Moore, Steve Parkhouse, Kelvin Gosnell, John Marshall & more, pencilled by Dave Gibbons, Steve Dillon, John Bolton, Paul Neary, David Lloyd, Stephen Baskerville & more, with cover artwork by Brian Bolland.
name: TPB

volume.name: Incredible Hulk: From the Marvel UK Vaults

description: Vince Morley lives on a knife-edge between reality and a corrupted, monstrous reflection he calls Cancertown, believing an inoperable brain tumor allows him to move between the two. Morley fights to save others from falling into Cancertown. Searching for a missing person named Daniel Grey, Morley is attacked by an escaped Cancertown resident called a Badmouth. When Morley discards the marker that the Badmouth has been using to track him, the creature chooses an alternate victim, dragging him into Cancertown. Morley has no choice but to follow.

Entering Cancertown to rescue a homeless man named Razor, Morley discovers the Corpsegrinder, a major player in Cancertown politics, in a state of distress. The Corpsegrinder grows in size in response to others' fear of him, and Morley finds him in his most terrible form. Psychologically incapable of fearing for his own life, Morley extracts the cause of the Corpsegrinder's current state - a terrified man left stranded in Cancertown. Leaving the Corpsegrinder's turf with the stranger, Morley finds Razor in the hands of another Cancertown player - the sinister, deadly Crosshair...

A simple search-and-rescue mission degenerates into a three-way stand-off as the demented Crosshair tries to trick the Corpsegrinder into killing Daniel Grey. Grey wears Crosshair's mark, and attacking the property of another Cancertown player brings grave consequences.

Recovering from the head injury inflicted by Daniel Grey, Morley sets about solving the mystery as best he can. Visiting Grey's wife, who is offering a $2000 reward for his return, Morley learns that he has disappeared before. Morley's worst suspicions are confirmed when, peering into the Cancertown version of Grey's office, he finds the man's links with Cancertown are just as strong as his own. Reeling from the discovery, Morley rushes out of Grey's house, only to fall straight into the most deadly corner of Cancertown: the home of Evil Twin...

Vince Morley is a man with big problems and a brain tumor like a baby's fist; living with one foot in a monstrous alternate world he calls Cancertown. When the lost and dispossessed of London start tripping over the same cracks in reality he spends his life avoiding, Morley realizes he must confront the residents of Cancertown - and risk finding his place among them.

The Tell Tale Heart and Other Stories

description: The first of the TALES Of TELLOS recounts the story of Pirate Queen, SERRA, and her first journey as a young girl aboard the Sheva Nova. Featuring the American debut of French artistic sensation, CRISSE!! Reknowned for his work on such titles as Kookaburra and Atalante, CRISSE lends his lively and whimsical style to this Tale of adventure on the High Seas! TALES Of TELLOS is a bi-monthly comic featuring solo stories both past and present of TELLOS colorful cast--with clues and events which lead directly into the next story arc by creators Mike Wieringo and Todd Dezago, TELLOS: SECOND COMING!

So you say that you've never picked up a copy of TELLOS, but you're wondering what all the noise is about...? Well, wonder no more! In this self-contained, 40 page yarn, Tellos scribe and Co-Creator, Todd Dezago teams up with sensational penciller, Craig Rousseau (Batman Beyond, Impulse) and inker extraordinaire, Norman Lee (SpyBoy), to bring you the wildest, rolickingest caper that ever fell out of these pages! Follow the misadventures of RIKK, the fox-slash-klepto, as he gets himself into more trouble than he's ever seen before! It is truly the "most worst thing" that's ever happened to him! This issue provides the perfect one-shot of fun or jumping on point for anyone who enjoys a good adventure! You'll kick yourself later...

It's never a typical day at the office for Envy Saint-Claire. Working for the AllTrades temp agency, every day she's someone else... sitting at someone else's desk, drinking someone else's coffee, talking to someone else's friends, doing someone else's job, living someone else's life. But only for a day. Everything in Envy's life is temporary, and that's just how she likes it. Meet Envy this December as she clocks into the Calvin C. Nelson HMO... the corporation where the inmates are literally running the asylum. "Cubes and Ladders" is the first issue in the new series, Temporary, by the Eisner-nominated writer of My Uncle Jeff and the Ignatz-nominated creator of Shuck.
name: Cubes and Ladders

The 0 issue contains a 10 page storyline that takes place BEFORE the original "Abuse of Humanity" hit mini series with all original art by Tony Daniel! The 1/2 issue contains a 16 page story by Tony Daniel and Steve Scott that takes place immediately AFTER the "Abuse of Humanity" miniseries concluded! Make your Tenth collection complete! This book will feature a brand new cover by Tony Daniel, featuring the Tenth, Espy and Zorina! Don't miss out!

Tyrants of Terror (12 pages)

"African gorillas have been known..." (1 page)

Death Dance (2 pages)

description: THE REBIRTH OF WITCHBLADE CONTINUES! The upstart creative team of TIM SEELEY (HACK/SLASH, BLOODSTRIKE) and DIEGO BERNARD (The Man With No Name) continues their hot run on Top Cow's flagship title! Even as Sara Pezzini tries to settle into her new life in Chicago, the Witchblade's talent for seeking out weirdness pulls her into bizarre case after bizarre case. This volume sees Pezzini dealing with mercenary mana-hunters, spirit realms, fantastical steampunk warriors, and the most distilled embodiment of evil she's ever encountered. And that's before the local cops and corrupt political system complicates her life... Featuring a complete cover gallery alongside a host of bonus content and extras, this trade is a must for anyone curious about Top Cow's REBIRTH! Collects WITCHBLADE #156-#160.

description:
What if the religious right... are right?

Therefore Repent! is a graphic novel set in a Chicago neighborhood after the Rapture. Once the Christians have floated bodily into the sky, life goes on pretty much as usual for the immoral majority... except that magic works, if you're willing to risk demonic mutations. CNN reports that Mr. Christ and Mr. Bush are on a speaking tour of the red states. And an angelic army appears to have been deployed to mop up the sinners. But through it all, outsiders Raven and Mummy face the possibility of a bigger problem than the end of the world: the end of their relationship.

In the tradition of The Book of Revelations, Therefore Repent!, courtesy of novelist Jim Munroe (Flyboy Action Figure Comes With Gasmask) and acclaimed artist Salgood Sam (Sea of Red) is a lurid, dark fantasy tale. By taking the apocryphal scripture as literal truth as the American powers-that-be claim to do the story also explores the political and spiritual ramifications of God abandoning humanity.
name: GN
